<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1210> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1210" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Varro in Gell. 17.21.43; Fast. Cap. (names entire); Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod., with Manlius for Mamilius; see Degrassi 42f., 117, 438f. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 48, no. 40." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1158> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1158" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 6.37160- ILS 9338 ([Q. ? Mam]ilius Q. f. Turrinu[s]), coopted in the consulship of a Cornelius Scipio ([- - - -Corn]elio P. f. Sci[pione- - - -]), as successor to C. Marcius Rutilus Censorinus (see 300).{211}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1156> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1156" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "This is the latest date possible for the cooptation of the successor in the priesthood of Marcius Rutilus Censorinus (see 300 and 265). The earliest is the consulship of a Scipio in 260, but 259 is also possible. In any case the filiation of Scipio was L. f. Dessau prefers the father Q. Mamilius, but the son C. Mamilius, Cos. 239, is also possible." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1155> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1155" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 6.37160- ILS 9338 ([Q. ? Mam]ilius Q. f. Turrinu[s]), coopted in the consulship of a Cornelius Scipio ([- - - -Corn]elio P. f. Sci[pione- - - -]), as successor to C. Marcius Rutilus Censorinus (see 300).{211}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1154> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1154" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "This is the latest date possible for the cooptation of the successor in the priesthood of Marcius Rutilus Censorinus (see 300 and 265). The earliest is the consulship of a Scipio in 260, but 259 is also possible. In any case the filiation of Scipio was L. f. Dessau prefers the father Q. Mamilius, but the son C. Mamilius, Cos. 239, is also possible." .
